<h1>About Us</h1>
<p>ProLog Soluções, Prestação de Serviços, Lda is an Angolan company specializing in logistics and
service provision, recognized for its ability to optimize and simplify logistics processes
for companies and organizations throughout the country. Founded with the vision of turning Angola's logistical
challenges into opportunities, ProLog gained significant visibility by taking over the distribution for several
convenience store chains, maintaining a daily national distribution network and ensuring
regular supply throughout the territory.</br></br>

The company is led by its founder and CEO, an experienced and visionary professional in the
logistics field, who, upon identifying the need for efficient solutions in the Angolan market, established
ProLog with a commitment to offering high-quality, personalized service. Under his leadership,
the company has become a benchmark for its innovative approach, developing logistics solutions
for remote and inhospitable regions of the country.</br></br>

Currently, ProLog has a dedicated team of about forty employees, who have been the
fundamental pillar of the company's growth and success. These committed professionals contribute
daily to the high standard of services that ProLog offers, from operations to customer
service. The management of ProLog values the continuous development of this team's skills,
investing in training and the improvement of their abilities, which also positions ProLog
as a benchmark in the logistics training sector in Angola.</br></br>

With a continuous focus on innovation and efficiency, ProLog adapts to the demands of a constantly
evolving market, promoting improvements at all stages of the logistics chain and establishing itself
as a trusted partner for companies seeking excellence and reliability in logistics and distribution.</p>
<br><br>
<h3>ProLog Soluções is certified by the following institutions: </h3>
<ul>
<li>Ministry of Transport (goods transport license)</li>

<li>Ministry of Mineral Resources, Oil and Gas (certification for service providers in the logistics sector)</li>

<li>National Agency for Oil, Gas and Biofuels (“ANPG”)</li>

<li>INEFOP (professional training center certification)</li>

<li>Ministry of Finance (state supplier certificate) </li>

<li>Holder of the ProLog Academy© Brand</li>
</ul></br></br>
<p>In 2024, ProLog Soluções joined the United Nations Global Compact (UNGC), committing to the
universal principles in the areas of human rights, labor, environment, and anti-corruption. By
aligning our efforts with these global goals and ethical principles, we contribute to a
more sustainable and inclusive future for all.</p>
